      "span_text": "Because the nuclear-encoded RPS16 was found to target both mt and cp in Arabidopsis, Lycopersicon, and Oryza [CITATION_2] , it is possible that the cp genome-encoded rps16 would not be maintained by selection and will eventually become lost in these lineages."
